Toulouse have won only one of their last 10 home games against Nantes in all competitions, that was on 7 April 2019.

title: Union Saint-Gilloise vs Newcastle United - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
synopsis: Union Saint-Gilloise will face off against an English side for the fifth time in European competition. After losing their first three, they beat Liverpool 2-1 at home in the most recent one in December 2023. Since losing their first game against a Belgian side in March 1970, Newcastle are unbeaten in their last nine such matches in European competition, winning eight of them. The most recent of those, however, came in a 2-2 draw against Club Brugge in November 2012 in the UEFA Europa League.

title: Qarabağ FK vs Copenhagen - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
synopsis: Qarabag and Copenhagen have faced each other on four previous occasions, with all four of those coming in qualifying matches. Copenhagen progressed from the first of those ties, before Qarabag progressed from the most recent. In 1998-99, Copenhagen won 10-0 over two legs against Qarabag in qualifying for the Cup Winners' Cup. Including qualifiers, this remains the Azerbaijani side’s heaviest ever defeat over two legs against a European side.

title: My Faith in Sport
synopsis: Ramadan is a crucial period in the Islamic calendar but fasting (Sawm) can provide complications for athletes who are trying to compete at the highest level. But to what extent is fasting a negative or can it actually aid performance? We look at the life and adaptation throughout Ramadan of Adam Azim – an unbeaten professional boxer from the UK, Fares El Bakh – a weightlifter who won Qatar’s first ever Olympic gold medal, and Zainab Alema – a rugby player who is aiming to become the first player to represent England wearing a hijab.Experts in Sports Science and Nutrition from Aspetar Clinic, Qatar also add detail of the physical impact athletes encounter during Ramadan

synopsis: Jannik Sinner vs Learner Tien. Sinner reaches his third straight Beijing final—his 30th tour-level title match and ninth in a row on hard courts. Teenager Tien, 19, is into his first ATP final after Medvedev retired in the semis. First meeting between the pair. Fast hard court favors Sinner’s first-strike baseline power; Tien counters with speed and resilience. 500 ranking points and the Beijing crown at stake.

title: Internazionale Milano vs Slavia Praha - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
synopsis: This will be the third meeting between Internazionale and Slavia Prague in European competition, with the previous two also coming in the UEFA Champions League in the 2019-20 group stage – Inter drew 1-1 at home, before winning 3-1 in the reverse fixture on the road. Slavia Prague have never won away to an Italian side in major European competition, losing seven of their eight attempts to date. The one game they did manage to avoid defeat in, however, came against Internazionale in September 2019.

title: Leeds United vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 6
synopsis: Leeds United have won all seven of their home league games against Bournemouth, scoring 18 goals in the process; it’s the most they’ve faced a side on home soil with a 100% win rate in their league history. After losing their first three, they beat Liverpool 2-1 at home in the most recent one in December 2023. Since losing their first game against a Belgian side in March 1970, Newcastle are unbeaten in their last nine such matches in European competition, winning eight of them. The most recent of those, however, came in a 2-2 draw against Club Brugge in November 2012 in the UEFA Europa League.

title: Atlético de Madrid vs Eintracht Frankfurt - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
synopsis: This will be the third meeting between Atlético Madrid and Eintracht Frankfurt in European competition, with the previous two coming in the last 16 of the 1975-76 Cup Winners’ Cup, and both won by the German side. The last German side to win away to Atlético Madrid in major European competition was Borussia Dortmund in October 1996. Since then, Atlético are unbeaten in 14 such matches, winning 10 of them.

title: Internazionale Milano vs Slavia Praha - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
synopsis: This will be the third meeting between Internazionale and Slavia Prague in European competition, with the previous two also coming in the UEFA Champions League in the 2019-20 group stage – Inter drew 1-1 at home, before winning 3-1 in the reverse fixture on the road. Slavia Prague have never won away to an Italian side in major European competition, losing seven of their eight attempts to date. The one game they did manage to avoid defeat in, however, came against Internazionale in September 2019.

title: Qarabağ FK vs Copenhagen - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
synopsis: Qarabag and Copenhagen have faced each other on four previous occasions, with all four of those coming in qualifying matches. Copenhagen progressed from the first of those ties, before Qarabag progressed from the most recent. In 1998-99, Copenhagen won 10-0 over two legs against Qarabag in qualifying for the Cup Winners' Cup. Including qualifiers, this remains the Azerbaijani side’s heaviest ever defeat over two legs against a European side.

The one game they did manage to avoid defeat in, however, came against Internazionale in September 2019.

title: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8

title: My Faith in Sport
synopsis: Ramadan is a crucial period in the Islamic calendar but fasting (Sawm) can provide complications for athletes who are trying to compete at the highest level. But to what extent is fasting a negative or can it actually aid performance? We look at the life and adaptation throughout Ramadan of Adam Azim – an unbeaten professional boxer from the UK, Fares El Bakh – a weightlifter who won Qatar’s first ever Olympic gold medal, and Zainab Alema – a rugby player who is aiming to become the first player to represent England wearing a hijab.Experts in Sports Science and Nutrition from Aspetar Clinic, Qatar also add detail of the physical impact athletes encounter during Ramadan

title: Newcastle United vs Nottingham Forest - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8

title: Gangwon FC (KOR) vs Shanghai Shenhua FC (CHN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD1
synopsis: This will be the first AFC Champions League Elite meeting between Gangwon and Shanghai Shenhua, with the former set to play their first-ever game in the competition; Shenhua have lost each of their last two matches against South Korean opposition in the Champions League Elite, another defeat here will see them equal their longest such run in competition history. Shanghai Shenhua lost their most recent AFC Champions League Elite match 0-4 to Kawasaki Frontale on 12 March 2025; failure to score against Gangwon will see them go scoreless in consecutive games for the first time in the competition since May 2011.

title: My Faith in Sport - Salah
synopsis: Exploring the importance of prayer within Islam, the episode begins with an overview of our seven athletes as they introduce themselves and why Islam is so important to them. We are also introduced to Omar Sulieman, a notable Imam, who acts as narration throughout the series and a guiding voice on the key principles of Islam. The life and career of Sofyan Amrabat is explored, showcasing his role as a key part of the Fenerbahce team in Turkey and the Moroccan national side. The Atlas Lions’ run to the semi-finals of the FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022 is explored, with the impact that Salah played in the team’s belief and positivity throughout the tournament.
